  "execution_target": "cpp",
  "optimization_notes": "Root cause is a combined Category B/C mismatch: iter2 touches a selective subset but reads lineitem measures through random rowid access and repeatedly executes expensive floating conversion/rounding per matched row, making main_scan latency and compute heavy. The revised plan keeps selective green-part and partsupp pruning, but materializes matched lineitem rowids with nation and scaled supplycost payload, sorts by rowid to turn lineitem measure access into locality-friendly sequential reads, and uses existing scaled int16 discount/quantity column versions to remove per-row floating conversion in the hot loop while preserving direct-array nation/year aggregation.",
  "correctness_anchors": {}
